  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sampanna - Resilient Nepal</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall summary of the project is to ensure earthquake resilient shelter construction of 367 most vulnerable HHs in Nilkantha Municipality of Dhading district is facilitated by providing required socio-technical support.More specifically the project aims to:
&#x2022; To provide socio-technical shelter assistance to the most vulnerable HHs of Nilkantha Urban Municipaility.
&#x2022; To facilitate coordination between vulnerable HHs, construction material suppliers, masons, bank and NRA/DLPIU at the district level.
&#x2022; To provide orientation to masons to ensure earthquake resilient shelter construction involving District Level Project Implementation Units ( DLPIU) along with technical assistants of project team.

The major objectives of this response and recovery of COVID 19 is to save the lives of most vulnerable people from the crucial status of this present situation through recovery assistance to the vulnerable HHs, health and sanitation kits distribution, and  raising awareness on the virus through radio jingles, IEC and banner, SMS, etc. the response activities will be in align with our present activities of the project primarily focusing in the area of DRR and Livelihood.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to provide socio-technical shelter assistance which will: 
&#x2022; Enable them to access the housing grant from NRA(National reconstruction Authority)  and procure construction materials within the avaiable grant amount
&#x2022; Complete the construction of their houses by 30th April, 2019
-Production of PSA ( Radio jingle) as directed by WHO and MoHP and broadcast from radio stations to create awareness to the community. 
-Preparation and dissemination of IECs and banners on its symptoms, preventions and precaution at the different locations of the market areas and community
-Support with hand washing buckets ,bathing shop, washing soap, sanitizers, masks, towel, gloves etc to at least 500 HHs.
-CASH and food support for the vulnerable HHs of Siddhalek RM.</narrative>
  </description>
